  "title": "Product Owner - BFSI domain",
  "description": "<p>Key Appointments</p><p>Manage changes in consumer platforms and support on key digital projects for business units including Investment, Marketing and Operations. Were looking for someone who thrives in a fast-paced environment, enjoys solving business problems through technology, and can manage day-to-day product operations while contributing to strategic outcomes.</p><p>Responsibilities</p><ul><li>Define and drive product vision, strategy, roadmap in alignment with business objective</li><li>Own and prioritize product backlog based on business needs requirements</li><li>Collaborate with cross-functional teams – Engineering, Operations, Marketing, Business stakeholders to translate requirements into product requirements</li><li>Review business processes and identify optimizing solutions/features</li><li>Develop user stories, document acceptance criteria, review test plan/scenarios, and perform user acceptance testing</li><li>Monitor deliverables and ensure timely and successful delivery of projects/initiatives</li><li>Present project plans, updates, and results to senior leadership team</li><li>Ensure compliance with all applicable laws and regulations relating to the above functional activities</li></ul><p>Experience</p><ul><li>Experience in investment products or investment-related domains, with an understanding of investment processes and digital enablement opportunities</li><li>Demonstrated experience managing third-party vendors or technology partners across delivery cycles</li><li>Over 5 years working experience in a Financial Services/Insurance industry</li><li>Proven track record of delivering complex digital products or platforms at scale</li><li>Strong experience working with multiple stakeholders in a fast-paced environment</li><li>Stakeholder management at senior/executive levels</li><li>Strong analytical and conceptual thinking skills</li><li>Self-motivated, flexible to change and resilient</li><li>Have a solution mindset, detail oriented and willingness to learn is a must</li></ul><p>Education</p><ul><li>Academic: Bachelors/Masters degree in Business or Digital/Tech related field</li><li>Agile knowledge or certifications</li><li>Worked with Project Management tools (e.g. Figma/Confluence/JIRA)</li></ul>",
